                  <AssemblerScript>[ENABLE]
{$lua}
showMessage([[##Explanation of the relic builder information:

Example:
7010700 : ro109|STD|N|CHARA|[Duchess] Successive dagger attack reprises event upon nearby enemies

Breakdown:
Effect_ID : Roll_Order | Compatibility | Req_Debuff | Roll_Group | In_Game_Name


- Effect_ID: The actual ID the game uses to determine what effect to use.
- Roll_Order: The order that relics should appear on a relic. They must be in order of lowest to highest. The lowest value will be in the attribute 1 slot, and the highest will be in attribute 3. Debuffs do not need to be in order. They have a roll order number, but do not use it.
- Compatibility: STD(Standard)/BTH(Both)/DoN(Deep Of Night). BTH is the only type that can be on either type of relic.
- Req_Debuff: Y/N, a Yes/No indicator if it needs a debuff. Do not put debuffs on things that don't need them, and do not forget to put them on things that do.
- Roll_Group: The group an effect is part of. Items with the same group can not be on the same relic, EXCEPT FOR "NONE" effects.
- In_Game_Name: The name players see in game.


## Important note:
Before editing any relic, do the following to make sure its safe:

- Unequip the relic you want to edit. You may have to remove it from your presets and any other characters with it.
- Check if it can be sold. Go to the sell menu and see if it can be highlighted. DO NOT SELL IT
- If it can be sold, exit the menu and reequip the relic. It is an RNG relic, and is safe.
- If it can not be sold, it is a unique relic. Do not edit this, they will flag your account.]])
